<br>
Mage pets were powerful in early Kunark, when the level 60 pets and the epic pet first became available. With Velious and then Luclin, boss mob level and AC went up a huge deal, but pet level and ATK stayed the same. As a result, our pets' damage output vs uber mobs has suffered greatly.<br>
<br>
Other caster classes were compensated for the Velious and Luclin changes - for instance, wizards got GB and DB, and mob resistances were significantly reduced, so nukes of all kinds could land. But a large part of magician damage is NOT nukes, it's melee, and nothing was done to fix that.<br>
<br>
The solution to the &quot;pet vs uber mob&quot; problem is not Burnout V in its current incarnation, because our pets' haste is already capped with BO4 and Muzzle. We need a pet buff spell, possibly no drop and located on mobs accessible only to high end guilds, that dramatically alters pet stats such as dex, atk, str, dual wield and offense skill, to significantly raise damage output against uber mobs. The spell could take the same 65pp reagent as banishment, to reduce the chance that more casual encounters would be trivialized.<br>
<br>
Another idea is summoned weapons with specialized procs and stat buffs that can only be wielded by pets, so mages can customize their pets to suit the encounter at hand. For instance, to raise the pet's damage output against uber giants, have a pet-only summoned sword with +50 dex that uses the same check as giantsbane, and procs a 250pt lure-based fire DD. You could make a whole range of swords based on this general idea.<br>
<br>
Something needs to be done Verant....please. While on the subject of pets, I would like to point out that &quot;dire charm&quot; is a pet skill in all but name, and since mages are supposed to be the masters of pets, we should be given a &quot;dire summoning&quot; skill to replace one of our many useless class skills, that does exactly the same thing as the enchanter version of &quot;dire charm&quot;.<br>
<br>
Datalore <p><CENTER>
