<br>
Druid DS:<br>
<br>
Oh wow, I'm so worried they might get a DS that is one point less than our best available DS and lasts a minute less too.  Not to mention that ours is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> mana free</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  These spells will almost certainly be raid level drops, and if you can get these spells, you can probably get the dagger with our upgrade on it.<br>
<br>
Nuke:<br>
<br>
Their nuke is only better on the surface.  First off, ours casts 0.5 sec faster, not a big deal but worth mentioning.  Secondly, any raid druid spends <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> most</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, not all, of their time healing, buffing, curing curses.  Nearly all druids at the level are spec. in alteration.  Mages use to have equal reason to be evoc or conjur at 60, but that's pretty quickly ending.  With Spell Casting Mastery 3, assuming numbers on the class skills area are right, would make it only 267 mana for us.  Meanwhile a druids alteration spec isn't changing their cost in any noticable way.<br>
<br>
Pet haste:<br>
<br>
If you think this spell sucks because we never use pets on raids, then you need a new guild.  The only mob that I can't use a pet on is Vyemm (this is from my choice, not raid leader's command), out of tons of raids.  If your guild doesn't let you use pets it is most likely because you either haven't shown yourself to be good at pet control, or the more likely case: your guild/raid leaders harbor old prejudces against pets that aren't true.  But hey, if they don't want the free damage, /shrug<br>
<br>
As for (this is mainly for WEZLOC) all this will do is make them miss faster.  Our pets currently do 1/3 of a well equipped rogue on uber mobs.  Rogues also attack twice as fast on raids.  Essentially all their weapons, when hasted, put them at 10 delay, where our pets have a delay of about 20.  Haste matters, and in a big way.  If we could give our pets enough haste so that their delay was equal to rogues, they'd do 2/3 of a rogues damage. <p>~~
